abstract: As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
snippet: As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — As the Senate lurched toward a vote to acquit President Donald Trump on impeachment charges, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo played clean-up in the country at the center of the inquiry on Friday.
headline_main: Pompeo Plays Clean-Up in Ukraine as Trump Trial Nears End
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Plays Clean-Up in Ukraine as Trump Trial Nears End

abstract: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
snippet: Mr. Biden’s attack on his rival in Iowa came hours after another leading candidate, Pete Buttigieg, criticized both men, in a day of sparring that underscored the pressure they all face to excel in Monday’s caucuses.
lead_paragraph: PELLA, Iowa — In one of his most direct confrontations yet with his top rival in the Iowa caucuses, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Thursday called out Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont for not being a Democrat even as Mr. Sanders makes a competitive run for that party’s presidential nomination, and Mr. Biden also jabbed Mr. Sanders’s record on gun control in among his most detailed remarks on the matter to date.

abstract: With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
snippet: With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
lead_paragraph: WAUKEE, Iowa — With four days until the Iowa caucuses, Joe Biden is looking beyond his Democratic rivals and taking square aim at President Donald Trump as the two men campaign within miles of each other on the same day.
headline_main: Aiming at Trump, Biden Says a President's Character Matters
headline_print_headline: Aiming at Trump, Biden Says a President's Character Matters

abstract: Bernie Sanders was endorsed Thursday by the 200,000-member American Postal Workers Union, an influential group that also backed the Vermont senator's presidential bid against Hillary Clinton during the 2016 Democratic presidential primary.
snippet: Bernie Sanders was endorsed Thursday by the 200,000-member American Postal Workers Union, an influential group that also backed the Vermont senator's presidential bid against Hillary Clinton during the 2016 Democratic presidential primary.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Bernie Sanders was endorsed Thursday by the 200,000-member American Postal Workers Union, an influential group that also backed the Vermont senator's presidential bid against Hillary Clinton during the 2016 Democratic presidential primary.
headline_main: Postal Workers Union With 200,000 Members Endorses Sanders
headline_print_headline: Postal Workers Union With 200,000 Members Endorses Sanders

abstract: U.S. Senate Republicans on Thursday tried to shift the focus of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial to the unnamed government official whose whistleblower complaint about Trump's dealings with Ukraine spurred the drive to remove him from office.
snippet: U.S. Senate Republicans on Thursday tried to shift the focus of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial to the unnamed government official whose whistleblower complaint about Trump's dealings with Ukraine spurred the drive to remove him from of...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Republicans on Thursday tried to shift the focus of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial to the unnamed government official whose whistleblower complaint about Trump's dealings with Ukraine spurred the drive to remove him from office.
headline_main: Impeachment Trial Turns to Whistleblower Ahead of Possible Weekend Finish

abstract: Strategic Iowa trips, a Sanders cash haul, Facebook ads: This is your morning tipsheet.
snippet: Strategic Iowa trips, a Sanders cash haul, Facebook ads: This is your morning tipsheet.
lead_paragraph: With the caucuses looming, any space in Iowa can become a political venue. Take, for example, this museum that sells historical furniture, RVP-1875, which hosted a Buttigieg event on Wednesday in Jefferson, Iowa.

headline_main: Impeachment, Coronavirus, Brexit: Your Thursday Briefing

abstract: Supporters of the former vice president say he can win back union members who rejected Hillary Clinton. But he must overcome some hard feelings first.
snippet: Supporters of the former vice president say he can win back union members who rejected Hillary Clinton. But he must overcome some hard feelings first.
lead_paragraph: On the campaign trail, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has highlighted the first two years of the Obama administration as a time when he helped enact sweeping legislation to widen access to health care and revive the economy, accomplishments most Democrats revere.
